data.description:
This classic 1978 home has been transformed into an extraordinary space that anyone would love to call home!! It's warm and inviting with it's cozy wood stove, knotty pine ceilings, floor to ceiling windows, family room plus a den, dining room and kitchen overlook the back yard. The master bedroom includes a full bath, there's also a separate seating area with a beautiful sink and faucet within the bedroom. From the bedroom you step out onto a huge covered patio, this space is completely private and if you ever dreamed of creating an outdoor living space....this is it, with a large koi pond and water feature, the small orchard of apple, cherry, peach and pear trees along with blueberry bushes and asparagus, it's a quiet and peaceful space where you're able to relax and let the stresses of the day, melt away. 
Other features include:
Induction Oven - requires magnetic pans.
2 Koi Ponds - Owner will maintain them.
Compost Bin.
Garden Beds.
Electricity Included.
2 R.V. Spaces.
Large Garden Shed.
Sprinklers and Drip System.
Please fill out your applications on our website and not on zillow, we don't charge a fee and process time is typically an hour or less, I run them on a first come first serve basis so it's fair for everyone. Once approved, we'll schedule your tour right away. The home is available now so please do not fill out applications unless you're ready to move right away, within two weeks as I cannot hold the property longer than that without rent. Thank you!
NEW PHOTOS COMING SOON!

Owner pays electricity and they will maintain the Koi ponds. The Lease is for 15 Months so it doesn't end in the wintertime next year. We prefer long term tenants as there are no intentions of selling.
